עבר  -  עבוּר / ‛âbûr  ‛âbûr / aw-boor', aw-boor'
=== Etymology ===

Passive participle of {{HH|5674}}; 

properly crossed, that is, (abstractly) transit; used only adverbially on account of, in order that: - because of, for (. . . ‘s sake), (intent) that, to.